rComments: Awesome professor who adores using technology to improve the learning experience. While there are few things graded (and thus, worth quite a lot each), the marking is extremely fair. The midterm had a few tricky questions, but overall this class was a great experience. I would take another course with M. Séror again in the future.
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', 'Gives good feedback', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: Jeremie is my favourite prof. He's very kind and his lectures are more like conversations with the students.  I love his teaching style as well as his exam format. As long as you listen in class and understand the subject you're sure to do well. He's very approachable and he gets on the same level as his students. He makes learning and teaching fun
Oral French class - hated it. Very strict marker. Nice man. Cares about students but talks too much. Didn't learn anything. Don't take his classes if you want to make progress.

Do NOT take a class with Seror if you want to learn in an non-intimidating class! He draws names from hats to get you to speak (oral French) instead of organizing small talking groups that are less intimidating. He micromanages a LOT. It makes assignments difficult. He is creative but frustrating.

Séror is a nice man. However, he micro-manages to an insane amount, making projects difficult to get started. He is organized but controlling, and I ended up severely disliking his oral French classes. His strategies for getting people to talk are not conducive to a helpful learning environment, and there were too many group projects. Hard marker.

Seror is an amazing prof! The class consisted of presentations, so sometimes attending class seemed pointless. He is a strict marker, just make sure you follow his guidelines and you will do good. I also recommend seeing him after hours and he will actually edit your presentations so you can do better! Overall, great prof.
Great teacher...Cares about his students although he is strict.

While I agree with the last person that this class wasn't totally necessary it did help me, even if it was just to get me to speak French more often. Jérémie was really nice and seemed like he knew what he was talking about, although there wasn't much opportunity to prove that. I have him again this year so we'll see!

Absolute waste of time, don't even bother registering for this class. While Professor Seror is a nice man, you do presentations for the entire semester and don't learn anything useful. His marking is strict too, making this class a double whammy. Avoid at all costs!
